list.item:
Article 15. The following articles
                                    may be imported in reasonable quantities after analysis and
                                    joint certification by Government-registered medical
                                    practitioners, druggists and chemists as to their proper use and
                                    after report to and further examination by the customs
                                    authorities: Morphine; cocaine and hypodermic syringes;
                                    antiopium pills containing morphine, opium or cocaine; stovaine;
                                    heroin; strychnine; thebaine; cghanja; hashish; bhang; cannabis indica; tincture of opium;
                                    laudanum; codeine; dionin; and all other derivatives of opium
                                    and cocaine.
